MEDICAL INSURANCE POLICY

Purpose
The company provides medical insurance coverage to support employee health and well-being.

Coverage Eligibility
All full-time employees are eligible for medical insurance from their date of joining.

Dependent Coverage
Coverage includes the employee, spouse, and up to two dependent children.

Hospitalization Coverage
The policy covers hospitalization expenses up to USD 100,000 per year.

Outpatient Benefits
Employees may claim outpatient consultation expenses up to USD 1,000 annually.

Preventive Health Checkups
Employees are eligible for one annual preventive health checkup.

Emergency Services
Emergency ambulance services and emergency room treatment are covered under the policy.

Claim Process
Employees must submit insurance claims through the company insurance portal within 30 days of treatment.

Exclusions
Cosmetic procedures, non-prescribed treatments, and experimental therapies are not covered unless specifically approved.

Insurance Provider
The company medical insurance plan is administered by Global Health Insurance Services.
